claim.claim-text:
1. A semiconductor memory comprising: 
a first control signal line controlling a selection from row addresses; 
a second control signal line controlling a selection from column addresses; 
a first transfer gate control mechanism cutting off the first control signal line when a predetermined number of control signals are determined as an abnormal signal; and 
a second transfer gate control mechanism cutting off the second control signal line when a predetermined number of control signals are determined as an abnormal signal.

4. A semiconductor memory comprising: 
plurality of external control signal lines; 
a word line coupled to plurality of memory cells; 
a pair of bit lines coupled to plurality of memory cells; 
a word line selection controller for controlling a selection from the word line; 
a bit line selection controller for controlling a selection from the pair of bit lines; 
a first control signal line controlling a transmission of designated row address to the word line selection controller; 
a second control signal line controlling a transmission of designated column agrees to the bit line selection controller; 
a first transfer gate mechanism cutting off the first control signal line and precharging the first control signal line so that the voltage of the first control signal line equals a power supply voltage when signals passing through some of the external control signal line indicating an abnormal state; and 
a second transfer gate mechanism cutting off the second control signal line and precharging the second control signal line so that the voltage of the second control signal line equals to the power supply voltage when signals passing through some of the external control signal line indicating an abnormal state.

9. A semiconductor memory comprising: 
a plurality of external control signal lines; 
a word line coupled to plurality of memory cells; 
a word line selection mechanism controlling a selection from the word line; 
a control signal line controlling a selection from row addresses; and 
a transfer gate control mechanism precharging the control signal line so that the voltage of the control signal line equals to a power supply voltage.

11. A semiconductor memory comprising: 
a plurality of external control signal lines; 
a word line coupled to plurality of memory cells; 
a pair of bit lines coupled to plurality of memory coils; 
a word line selection means controlling a selection from the word line; 
a first control signal line controlling a selection from row addresses; 
a bit line selection means controlling a selection from the pair of bit line; 
a second control signal line controlling a selection from column addresses; 
a detector generating a signal in accordance with a signal showing the external control signal line to be in an abnormal state; and 
a voltage setting means charging the first and second control signal line, and controlled by a signal generated from the detector.

12. A semiconductor memory comprising: 
a plurality of external control signal line; 
a word line coupled to plurality of memory cells; 
a pair of bit lines coupled to plurality of memory cells; 
a word line selection means controlling a selection from the word line; 
a control signal line controlling the word lane selection means; 
a detector in a business generating a signal in accordance with a signal showing the external control signal line to be in an abnormal state; and 
a voltage setting means charging the control signal line, and controlled by a signal generated from the detector.

13. A semiconductor device comprising; 
a first control signal line controlling a selection from a word line; 
a second control signal line controlling a selection from a pair of bit lanes; 
a voltage control circuit precharging the first and second control signal lines; and 
a power-on signal generator generating constant voltage during the voltage control circuit precharges the first and second control signal lines.

16. A method for protecting semiconductor memory comprising the steps of: 
transmitting a first control signal along a first control signal line controlling a selection from row addresses; 
transmitting a second control signal along a second control signal line controlling a selection of column addresses; 
cutting off the first control signal when a predetermined number of control signals are determined to be in an abnormal state; and 
cutting off the second control signal when a predetermined number of control signals are determined to be in an abnormal state.
